. Sutphin Boulevard, at the S.E. corner of Ninetieth Ave., showing the William A. Warnock house; owned by A. A. De Graw.

April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Sutphin Boulevard, at the S. E. corner of 90th Avenue, showing the William A. Warnock House, built by Aaron Degrauw. Warnock was President of the Village of Jamaica from 1891 to 1893. He also resided in the Judd Mansion, also known as the Keteltas House, in 1896.

1925

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
